    • Field Detail

      • logger

        private static final org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger logger
        Logger registered for Lane class.

      • type

        private Lane.TYPE type
        Type of this lane. Which lane is it?

      • team

        private int team
        Team that this lane belongs to? Lanes are obviously not team related, but we have pathcorners, that define the lane and the pathcorners belong to one of the teams. (so does the lanes then)

      • pathCorners

        private ArrayList<PathCorner> pathCorners
        Arraylist of path corners. They will be sorted later, so that the one closest to base is at the start.

      • towers

        private ArrayList<Tower> towers
        List of towers. Those will be sorted, so that first tower is the one closest to the base.

      • laneCreeps

        private LinkedHashMap<Integer,Creep> laneCreeps
        List of friendly creeps currently on the lane. Can be iterated, the older creeps will be at the start.

      • meleeRax

        private Rax meleeRax
        Melee barracks.

      • rangedRax

        private Rax rangedRax
        Ranged barracks.

      • centerPathCorner

        private PathCorner centerPathCorner
        Index of path corner, that is approximately in the middle of the lane. //

      • pushedRatio

        private double pushedRatio
        Range of -1 to 1 indicating if lane is pushed beyond center of the lane. 0 if the lane is on center of the lane. (or no creeps are spawned yet)

        Initializes the center of lane. This information is hard coded :(. I have not found a better way how to do this, because every path looks a bit different. So this must be tweaked if the map changes dramatically.
